The paper proposes a new paradigm for probabilistic reasoning, which is a fundamental topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces a family of probabilistic logics, which falls under the category of mathematical logic (cs.LO). The paper discusses soundness, completeness, and justification, which are important concepts in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the Dempster-Shafer theory of evidence, which is a well-known approach in cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper explores possibilities for novel synthesis of ideas in probabilistic reasoning, which is a topic in systems and control (cs.SI).
